-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 03, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104scm1665702714238.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/scm1665702714238.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/scm1665702714238.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"scm1665702714238\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Library </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"scm1665702714238__library_317108\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Library is a Main Development Object that holds a collection of objects of the same\n      type that can be accessed or reused by other objects, either during development or at runtime. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scm1665702714238__p_d96527e1_d96528e1_d96529e1\">Runtime libraries contains objects that are resolved in\n         the application at runtime, such as Messages and Global ProcScripts.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scm1665702714238__p_d96530e1_d96531e1_d96532e1\">Development libraries contain objects that are used or\n         resolved during development, such as Modeled Field Interfaces, Snippets and IncludeScripts.\n         These libraries can only contain objects of the same type.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scm1665702714238__p_d96533e1_d96534e1_d96535e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"kee1692183917031.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kee1692183917031.html\" title=\"Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included.\">Libraries</a>.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scm1665702714238__topic_d64567e1_d64568e1_d64569e1_d64570e1_d64571e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d388055e69\"> Characteristics </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ulo1665702550460.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html\" title=\"A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\">Development Object</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"srw1665702550375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/srw1665702550375.html\" title=\"A Main Development Object is a Development Object that has no parent object, is maintained using a dedicated editor, and can be saved and exported as a single unit, with all its children.\">Main Development Object</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Development libraries: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vhx1665702714312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vhx1665702714312.html\" title=\"A Snippet Library contains code Snippets that can copied and pasted into your code during development.\">Snippet Library</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hdr1665702713345.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hdr1665702713345.html\" title=\"An IncludeScript Library contains IncludeScript objects, which can be inserted into ProcScript using the #include directive and are resolved during compilation.\">IncludeScript Library</a>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">Runtime libraries: <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wcl1665702709004.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wcl1665702709004.html\" title=\"A Global ProcScript Library contains Global ProcScript objects, which are linked into components at runtime when called from other ProcScript in the application.\">Global ProcScript Library</a>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">URI format:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"scm1665702714238__table_d10736e1_d10737e1_d10738e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scm1665702714238__p_d96539e1_d96540e1_d96541e1\">The Library is an abstract data type that generalizes\n            typed libraries. It specializes Main Development Object in the following ways:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39260e1_d39261e1_d39262e1\">It contains development objects of a single type\n               that are shared across the application. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39263e1_d39264e1_d39265e1\">It does not have code containers. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"scm1665702714238__topic_d64572e1_d64573e1_d64574e1_d64575e1_d64576e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d388055e284\"> Properties </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"scm1665702714238__p_d96545e1_d96546e1_d96547e1\">Object Properties:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39266e1_d39267e1_d39268e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jrq1665702585385.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jrq1665702585385.html\" title=\"Name of the development object, which uniquely identifies it.\">Name</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39269e1_d39270e1_d39271e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"owq1665702585461.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/owq1665702585461.html\" title=\"Type of Development Object. Read only.\">Type</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39272e1_d39273e1_d39274e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ybn1665702585544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ybn1665702585544.html\" title=\"Complete URI of the Development Object. Read only.\">Location</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39275e1_d39276e1_d39277e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xrw1665702585620.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrw1665702585620.html\" title=\"Use this property to briefly describe the development object in up to 256 Unicode characters.\">Description</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39278e1_d39279e1_d39280e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ipc1665702585697.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ipc1665702585697.html\" title=\"Use this property to provide comments or instructions for the selected development object. You can use the toolbar and standard Windows keyboard shortcuts to format the text, copy and paste, and undo and redo edits.\">Documentation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39281e1_d39282e1_d39283e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uaj1665702714384.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uaj1665702714384.html\" title=\"This property determines the purpose of the object during development. It is used to separate application objects from templates and palettes.\">Purpose</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\">Source Properties:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"scm1665702714238__li_d39284e1_d39285e1_d39286e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cnn1665702762358.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cnn1665702762358.html\" title=\"Read-only property the records the date and time when the object was last modified. The value is set by Uniface.\">Date Modified</a></li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kee1692183917031.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Libraries</a><p>Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615813\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615813\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Library Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 03, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Library A Library is a Main Development Object that holds a collection of objects of the same type that can be accessed or reused by other objects, either during development or at runtime. Runtime libraries contains objects that are resolved in the application at runtime, such as Messages and Global ProcScripts. Development libraries contain objects that are used or resolved during development, such as Modeled Field Interfaces, Snippets and IncludeScripts. These libraries can only contain objects of the same type. For more information, see Libraries . Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: — Main Development Object? Yes Part of: — Contains: Development Object , Property Generalization: Main Development Object Specializations: Development libraries: Snippet Library , IncludeScript Library Runtime libraries: Global ProcScript Library Compilation Output: — URI format: — The Library is an abstract data type that generalizes typed libraries. It specializes Main Development Object in the following ways: It contains development objects of a single type that are shared across the application. It does not have code containers. Properties Object Properties: Name Type Location Description Documentation Purpose Source Properties: Date Modified Related Links Libraries Libraries are collections of objects that can be shared in some way, either during development, or at runtime. They are main development objects, so whenever they are saved or exported, all the objects that they contain are included. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}